Siluanov Sees 5.4% Deficit Next Year If Crude Prices Average $60

-- B y   S c o t t   R o s e
-- 
2011-10-10T08:01:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/siluanov-sees-5-4-deficit-next-year-if-crude-prices-average-60.html
Russia may run a budget deficit of
5.4 percent of gross domestic product if oil prices average $60
a barrel and post a fiscal gap of 2.5 percent with $90 oil,
acting Finance Minister Anton Siluanov told reporters in Moscow
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Rose in Moscow at 
 rrose10@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
